output.crosstab_text:
For first degree graduates of all subjects, one year after graduation, Human health and social work activities was the most common industry for all ethnicities.

The industry with the largest range in proportions was Human health and social work activities where Black ethnicity graduates had the highest proportion and Mixed ethnicity graduates had the lowest proportion. The industry with the largest range in median earnings was Activities of households as employers - undifferentiated goods-and services-producing activities of households for own use where Mixed ethnicity graduates had the highest median earnings (£27,700) and Black ethnicity graduates had the lowest median earnings (£ 9,900). The group with the highest earnings was Asian ethnicity graduates who worked in the Human health and social work activities industry (median earnings of £28,800).
output.crosstab_title: Industry of graduate employment for graduates of all subjects by ethnicity, one year after graduation, male and female first degree graduates from HE providers, 2020/21 tax year.
